Terms & Conditions

                    Mandarin Oriental Hotel Group Limited

                      Fans of M.O. Terms and Conditions

                                January 2018


    1. General Terms and Conditions
         1. The Fans of M.O. Programme (the “Programme”) is operated and
            administered by Mandarin Oriental Hotel Group Limited and its
            affiliates (collectively, “MOHG”). The Programme will provide
            guests of MOHG-managed hotels that are participating in the
            Fans of M.O. Programme (“MO Hotels”) the opportunity to
            receive certain benefits from MO Hotels from time to time. The
            terms and conditions applicable to the Programme are set out
            in these “Terms and Conditions”.
         2. Members acknowledge and agree that their participation in the
            Programme is subject to and contingent on Member’s acceptance
            of the MOHG Privacy Policy found at:
            www.mandarinoriental.com/privacy-policy, Ad and Cookie Policy
            found at: www.mandarinoriental.com/cookie-policy, and Legal
            Notices found at: www.mandarinoriental.com/legal-notices.
            These policies and notices are deemed to be incorporated into
            these Terms and Conditions.
         3. Membership to the Programme will only be granted to individual
            persons. MOHG may grant or deny membership in the Programme in
            MOHG’s sole discretion, without the need for any reason or
            explanation. Individuals must be at least 18 years of age or
            have reached the age of majority, if older under applicable
            local laws. It is a Member’s sole and exclusive responsibility
            to ensure that they comply with these age requirements.
            Corporations and/or organizations are not eligible to enrol in
            the Programme.
         4. Individuals who apply for and are granted membership in the
            Programme (“Member” or “Members”) are eligible for Programme
            benefits when they stay at a MO Hotel as a paying guest and
            for exclusive Member-only access and offers (collectively
            “Benefits”). All Members acknowledge and agree that they must
            satisfy the age requirements specified above in order to
            legitimately benefit from membership in the Programme.
         5. Membership in the Programme is free, has no cash value and is
            not commissionable. No purchase is required to apply for
            membership in the Programme.
         6. Enrolment in the Programme can be made online at
            www.mandarinoriental.com/fans-of-mo (“Programme Gateway”). By
            enrolling and / or participating in the Programme, Members
            agree to abide by these Terms and Conditions. To enrol in the
            Programme, guests must provide their first and last names as
            well as a valid email address and a password. Upon successful
            enrolment, Members will be assigned an individual Member ID.
         7. MOHG reserves the right to amend or modify the Programme,
            Programme structure and/or these Terms and Conditions at its
            sole discretion at any time, with or without notice. Programme
            modifications may include changes to Benefits, redemption
            requirements and the features of special offers. A Member’s
            continued use of the Programme will constitute acceptance of
            the amendments and modifications.
         8. For specific Programme questions, please direct all
            communications to Member Services at: FansOfMO@mohg.com.
         9. MOHG may immediately suspend or terminate a Member’s
            membership in the Programme at any time without notice and/or
            for any reason, and in MOHG’s sole discretion; including
            without limitation, if MOHG suspects (even if not proven) the
            Member has breached or violated these Terms and Conditions,
            engaged in misuse or wrongdoing in connection with the
            Programme, acted in a fraudulent, inappropriate, hostile or
            abusive manner, failed to pay any amount due to MOHG or any MO
            Hotel, acted in a manner inconsistent with any applicable law,
            regulation, rule or ordinance, or resides in or relocates to a
            country where membership is prohibited under applicable law.
            Such termination will result in an automatic forfeiture of any
            Benefits and Member will no longer be able to participate in
            the Programme (a record of such termination will be retained
            on MOHG’s records). Nothing contained in these Terms and
            Conditions shall limit MOHG in the exercise of its legal or
            equitable rights or remedies.
        10. Members acknowledge and agree that MOHG reserves the sole and
            exclusive right to the interpretation of these Terms and
            Conditions. In the event of any dispute with Members, the
            determination of MOHG of the dispute will be final, without
            right of further appeal.
        11. Some MOHG-managed hotels will not be participating in the Fans
            of M.O. Programme and therefore will not provide the Benefits
            to Members. As at 13 August, 2018 the MOHG-managed hotels that
            are not participating in the Fans of M.O. Programme are as
            follows: Hotel Santiago.
    2. Programme Membership
         1. Membership in the Programme is free and available to
            individuals residing in countries that legally permit
            participation in such programmes. Participation in the
            Programme indicates acceptance of these Terms and Conditions
            as well as any changes or modifications made to them by MOHG
            from time to time.
         2. No Member may transfer, assign or otherwise dispose of their
            Programme membership to a third party.
         3. By enrolling in the Programme, consent is given to MOHG to
            collect and use Member’s personal information in connection
            with the Programme. By providing contact information, Members
            agree to receive marketing communications, including offers
            and promotional messages, from MOHG and MO Hotels.
         4. MOHG is not responsible for communication errors resulting
            from a change to Member’s email address or contact
            information. Any change to Member’s email address should be
            made to Member Services. Members can log into their online
            account on the Programme Gateway.
         5. Members are solely responsible for ensuring that access to
            their online membership in the Programme is protected using a
            confidential and strong/secure password, and such password
            must not be disclosed to any other party. MOHG cannot be held
            liable for the consequences of any unauthorized access to a
            Member’s account.
         6. Providing fictitious, incorrect or false information may
            result in termination of your Programme membership and
            forfeiture of all Benefits.
         7. An individual is not permitted to have more than one
            Membership. In the event more than one account number is
            assigned to the same individual, the duplicate account may be
            cancelled by MOHG, and only the Benefits, excluding any
            welcome Benefits, will be transferred to the remaining account
            as determined by MOHG in its discretion.
         8. Membership may be cancelled by a Member at any time by
            notifying Member Services by email. Cancellation may take up
            to two (2) weeks to finalize. Upon cancellation, membership
            will be deactivated and any offers or unused Benefits will be
            forfeited.
         9. Any Membership that has been inactive for a period of not less
            than five years may be terminated by MOHG, in its sole
            discretion, with any unused Benefits being forfeited.
            Membership will also automatically terminate upon the death of
            the Member, with any unused Benefits being forfeited.

    3. Data Privacy and Membership Communications
         1. Member accepts and explicitly agrees that personal information
            which is supplied by or on behalf of Member when enrolling for
            membership in the Programme and/or supplied to and/or obtained
            by MOHG during the course of the Member’s membership in the
            Programme, will be processed by MOHG in accordance with the
            MOHG Privacy Policy (found at:
            www.mandarinoriental.com/privacy-policy). In particular, but
            without limitation, MOHG processes Members’ personal
            information as follows:
               o MOHG will collect, retain and process Members’ names,
                 contact details, demographics, preferences (including
                 food allergies, medical conditions and other sensitive
                 data) and transaction data (collectively, “PII”) from the
                 information Members provide MOHG and the MO Hotels, and
                 from personal interactions Members have with service
                 staff at properties managed by MOHG, in order for MOHG to
                 inform Members of and/or provide Members with the
                 services MOHG thinks Members may be interested in or that
                 Members may request from MOHG and/or the MO Hotels from
                 time to time.
               o Members’ PII will be shared with MOHG’s global network of
                 companies and the service providers that assist MOHG with
                 administering Members’ PII (collectively, “MO Hotel
                 Network”). Accordingly, a Member’s PII may be transferred
                 to, processed in and stored at a country outside a
                 Member’s country of residence (including outside the EEA,
                 if the Member is an EEA resident).
               o The MO Hotel Network will contact Members by letter,
                 email, phone, text and/or fax to inform Members of news
                 and promotions regarding hotels, travel, food & beverage,
                 spa, conferencing, fashion and real estate products and
                 services that are related to or associated with the
                 Programme and/or MO Hotels.
         2. Members may opt-out of receiving communications under the
            Programme by updating their online Member profile via the
            Programme Gateway or by directly notifying Member Services.
            Any other methods of opting-out will not be valid or
            acceptable unless otherwise agreed to in writing by MOHG.
            However, in exercising such opt-out, the Member’s membership
            in the Programme may be terminated by MOHG and/or Member’s
            access to Benefits may be limited, terminated or otherwise
            restricted as a result.

         3. Programme communications will be sent to the Member’s mailing
            address, email address, phone number or such other contact
            details as provided in the Member’s account. Members are
            solely responsible for keeping their email, phone numbers,
            mailing addresses and other contact details current, and for
            keeping all such contact details secure against unauthorized
            access.

         4. Members may change personal details held by MOHG at any time
            by accessing their Programme membership account via the
            Programme Gateway. MOHG may require Members to send supporting
            documentation satisfactory to MOHG, prior to allowing certain
            changes to Members personal details (e.g., legal name
            changes).

         5. MOHG may disclose details of Members’ membership in the
            Programme to the extent required by applicable laws and
            regulations, or as may be required by court order.

    4. Programme Benefits
         1. Members acknowledge and agree that, with respect to Members’
            use and enjoyment of Benefits at a MO Hotel: (a) the actual
